-- Pound Drops Versus Dollar as U.K. Retail Sales Unexpectedly Fall
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2013-05-22T08:37:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-22/pound-drops-versus-dollar-as-u-k-retail-sales-unexpectedly-fall.html
The pound extended declines against
the dollar and euro after a report showed U.K. retail sales
unexpectedly fell in April.  Sterling weakened as much as 0.5 percent to $1.5075, the
lowest level since April 4. It was at $1.5083 at 9:36 a.m.
London time. It declined 0.7 percent to 85.74 pence per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
